{"id": "ChIJBxNMwDfFwoARY3YYjb1o3z8", "rating": 3.9, "priceLevel": "PRICE_LEVEL_INEXPENSIVE", "userRatingCount": 967, "displayName": {"text": "Kang Kang Food Court", "languageCode": "en"}, "editorialSummary": {"text": "Chinese fast-food spot serving soup, dumplings, noodle dishes & more in a food court setting.", "languageCode": "en"}, "reviews": [{"name": "places/ChIJBxNMwDfFwoARY3YYjb1o3z8/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xkS1QwMTNUVWxOWVRoS1NHUlZTR3BoUm5JNFgyYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Kang Kang Food Court is a great place to get very good Shanghai  Chinese food at a reasonable price. The atmosphere is not very good but there’s plenty of seating. Bring your own wet naps to clean the tables. It can also get a bit noisy depending on who’s there. But there’s always to go. If you get the Shanghai fried buns, make sure you eat them there because they’re delicious fresh but not so much when they’re not.\n\nI highly recommend you give this place a try for an authentic Shanghai comfort food dining experience!", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Kang Kang Food Court is a great place to get very good Shanghai  Chinese food at a reasonable price. The atmosphere is not very good but there’s plenty of seating. Bring your own wet naps to clean the tables. It can also get a bit noisy depending on who’s there. But there’s always to go. If you get the Shanghai fried buns, make sure you eat them there because they’re delicious fresh but not so much when they’re not.\n\nI highly recommend you give this place a try for an authentic Shanghai comfort food dining experience!", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Bill G", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/117661438251935703597/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9H81u-jhwAjHJ5r-fYzGuYceb9pzWtgDSziOJ7ku740x3a83W=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2026-05-09T18:03:24.533868348Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xkS1QwMTNUVWxOWVRoS1NHUlZTR3BoUm5JNFgyYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2xkS1QwMTNUVWxOWVRoS1NHUlZTR3BoUm5JNFgyYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c537c04c1307:0x3fdf68bd8d187663"}, {"name": "places/ChIJBxNMwDfFwoARY3YYjb1o3z8/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkaFNtTkZORmxGT1daTE4xTllXVGhEVlROcVFWRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "rating": 5, "text": {"text": "Must try. There are dishes here that I’ve never even seen before like mega sized glutinous rice balls (tong yuan) and fried glutinous rice mixed with soy milk. Get the pan fried buns and Shanghai moon cakes (savory with a flakey crust)! Juiciest dumplings and buns. Can’t go wrong here.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Must try. There are dishes here that I’ve never even seen before like mega sized glutinous rice balls (tong yuan) and fried glutinous rice mixed with soy milk. Get the pan fried buns and Shanghai moon cakes (savory with a flakey crust)! Juiciest dumplings and buns. Can’t go wrong here.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Jackie L", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/105579514665294683447/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrUU8NR8Z7z4TYMFsRfN8E7MvW8UncQx5UZHy122cTbKokJ3y0=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba4"}, "publishTime": "2025-11-14T19:02:44.101193942Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkaFNtTkZORmxGT1daTE4xTllXVGhEVlROcVFWRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT2pkaFNtTkZORmxGT1daTE4xTllXVGhEVlROcVFWRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c537c04c1307:0x3fdf68bd8d187663"}, {"name": "places/ChIJBxNMwDfFwoARY3YYjb1o3z8/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21WTlltZG1SRUk1ZFdWMFQwSmFYM3BIVnpSU2NYYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "rating": 3, "text": {"text": "I’ve gotten to eat here for years, after their outbreak with cockroaches & unprotected raw food near 120-130F, we went to try it again, we risked it for those Shanghai baos, however there is a bone on the receipt that came from the orange chicken, be careful of what you want to eat", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "I’ve gotten to eat here for years, after their outbreak with cockroaches & unprotected raw food near 120-130F, we went to try it again, we risked it for those Shanghai baos, however there is a bone on the receipt that came from the orange chicken, be careful of what you want to eat", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "Honey bunniuwu", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/102196979239239223870/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUr07AD_Ky8IUUBR2oLb8w8v2tdxuqJoEjWlzrBq86ZafkpsXDR0Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba2"}, "publishTime": "2026-04-19T07:14:57.705414381Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21WTlltZG1SRUk1ZFdWMFQwSmFYM3BIVnpSU2NYYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT21WTlltZG1SRUk1ZFdWMFQwSmFYM3BIVnpSU2NYYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c537c04c1307:0x3fdf68bd8d187663"}, {"name": "places/ChIJBxNMwDfFwoARY3YYjb1o3z8/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURqMUpTMTRBRRAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 years ago", "rating": 2, "text": {"text": "Updated 2024.04.29 From Chinatown, Los Angeles, we have taken one bus #76, about a 38 minutes ride to the restaurant across the street from the bus stop.\nInside was very warm, no air conditioning, cafeteria style with trays of food to select from or order off the menu.  Up to four items is USD 10.91.  The food quality was only average, not worth the time taken for a long bus ride for their food.  The sweet and sour and the pork belly was nice as expected.  The pan-fried soup dumplings were subpar, the dough was very thick compared with the amount of filling.  The house soup was very bland with almost no taste.  Twenty-five cent charge for hot tea, three percent charge for using a credit card.", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "Updated 2024.04.29 From Chinatown, Los Angeles, we have taken one bus #76, about a 38 minutes ride to the restaurant across the street from the bus stop.\nInside was very warm, no air conditioning, cafeteria style with trays of food to select from or order off the menu.  Up to four items is USD 10.91.  The food quality was only average, not worth the time taken for a long bus ride for their food.  The sweet and sour and the pork belly was nice as expected.  The pan-fried soup dumplings were subpar, the dough was very thick compared with the amount of filling.  The house soup was very bland with almost no taste.  Twenty-five cent charge for hot tea, three percent charge for using a credit card.", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "G L", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/110850296356097865285/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNBSR72Fa3fgY7LjS_2LuaaV0GN8Gg1kWkXvUgESk5ZTGZFQ=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo-ba7"}, "publishTime": "2024-04-30T05:22:34.986902Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURqMUpTMTRBRRAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURqMUpTMTRBRRAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c537c04c1307:0x3fdf68bd8d187663"}, {"name": "places/ChIJBxNMwDfFwoARY3YYjb1o3z8/reviews/Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT201SGIxWmpjVFpHYVdSUlZWUnFNWE5GTmtSR1ZtYxAB", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "rating": 3, "text": {"text": "This review is to not discourage but to set expectations appropriately. The pan fried bun is stellar but the wonton noodle soup is horrendous. Service is the definition of no frills to borderline rude. This is likely cultural but still jarring. Many received their food order before ours despite us ordering first. Bring cash to avoid the 3% surcharge of using a card. If you plan to dine in, the tables are classically sticky with ring marks from cups. There is plenty of parking in the back.\n\nTLDR:\nCome for the pan fried pork bao, bring cash, service is nearly nonexistent", "languageCode": "en"}, "originalText": {"text": "This review is to not discourage but to set expectations appropriately. The pan fried bun is stellar but the wonton noodle soup is horrendous. Service is the definition of no frills to borderline rude. This is likely cultural but still jarring. Many received their food order before ours despite us ordering first. Bring cash to avoid the 3% surcharge of using a card. If you plan to dine in, the tables are classically sticky with ring marks from cups. There is plenty of parking in the back.\n\nTLDR:\nCome for the pan fried pork bao, bring cash, service is nearly nonexistent", "languageCode": "en"}, "authorAttribution": {"displayName": "J. H", "uri": "https://www.google.com/maps/contrib/106992450196719511010/reviews", "photoUri": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKyI75N-GZryzrQD5j6PF4a5g9poD2VA7B5o2qBu8FTnSXR2Q=s128-c0x00000000-cc-rp-mo"}, "publishTime": "2026-01-06T00:54:51.007959573Z", "flagContentUri": "https://www.google.com/local/content/rap/report?postId=Ci9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT201SGIxWmpjVFpHYVdSUlZWUnFNWE5GTmtSR1ZtYxAB&d=17924085&t=1", "googleMapsUri": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m6!14m5!1m4!2m3!1sCi9DQUlRQUNvZENodHljRjlvT201SGIxWmpjVFpHYVdSUlZWUnFNWE5GTmtSR1ZtYxAB!2m1!1s0x80c2c537c04c1307:0x3fdf68bd8d187663"}], "photos": [{"name": "places/ChIJBxNMwDfFwoARY3YYjb1o3z8/photos/AWCwydh1xSd_f75Gkj1fNYeXJuLBqEynk8SZlN9mKo-bAvFYyoUIrjr3XJDSI-G-cLeQTgs8586ZX7c8xBL7sInKVzTq9pQKRv7QJK2jeoMV7gpvI2AUT0VRXyeCD1PQ7S4ThRlYKkFSbF9R0UgHeAeDbIL6TvvqREDrOE4L-uYsM0AE9vSWjU0YqKfG_qcyt